      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Heroes of Golarion pg. 18</em></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\"><img style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\" src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" />Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 3,000 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 20 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1 (5 ft.); <strong>Capacity</strong> 2</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3>\n<p>This double-barreled pistol variant has its barrel attached to its stock by a hinge, enabling ammunition to be loaded quickly and easily. Reloading a breech-loader is a standard action that reloads both barrels; the @Compendium[pf-content.pf-feats.5MEcO5qLxNgAM7zs]{Rapid Reload}&nbsp;feat reduces this to a move action.</p>",
